author: Russell Brand
description:
The BBC was caught editing a Trump speech to make it seem like he incited the Capitol riot — splicing two clips nearly an hour apart. This wasn’t a mistake; it was a worldview in action. When the press believes deceit is justified in the name of “defending democracy,” truth itself becomes expendable. From the “fine people” hoax to moral crusades that turn politics into theology, the media’s war on Trump reveals a deeper crisis: what happens when journalism stops reporting power and starts performing it?
